NOSTRADAMUS · N1 — the prophetic corpus catalogued (a tinfoil codex)
Copyright (c) 2026 David Lee Wise (ROOT0) / TriPod LLC — for the original commentary,
catalogue, design, the ACI/.dlw badges, and presentation.

The works of Michel de Nostredame (Nostradamus) — Les Prophéties (1555), the Almanacs,
the Preface to César, the Epistle to Henry II, and his other writings (1550–1568) — are
in the PUBLIC DOMAIN. This project quotes them minimally (favouring original commentary)
and reproduces no copyrighted modern translation.

HONEST SEAL: the famous "predictions" (Hister, Mabus, the three antichrists, the 1999
King of Terror, etc.) are LATER INTERPRETATIONS retrofitted onto cryptic verse. They are
presented here as lore and reception history, not as verified prophecy.

